y:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">3</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">Frustratingly, after almost two years and within a few months of my planned public exposure of the</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">ir negligence</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"> on the Court steps, N</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">etwork </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">ail</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"> decided to settle o</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">ut of Court and therefore avoid any damaging publicity. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">14</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">A few weeks later, upon return of my papers from the solicitors, I discovered a risk assessment that has been disclosed</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"> to my solicitor</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"> by N</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">etwork </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">R</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">ail</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt"> during </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">our case, </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">but </span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">this had not been se</span><span style="font-family:Helvetica; font-size:11pt">en</span><span styl